Description:
Modern living
A beautiful home offering the best in living, outdoor entertainment & location. High vaulted ceilings are a feature in the open plan kitchen, dining & living areas. Rendered feature fence, established bushes, stunning timber walk way steps to welcome guests & providing privacy from the street.
Modern kitchen of the best quality with Caesar stone bench tops, large preparation island, feature cupboards, pot draws with soft closers. A large five burner gas cook top & 900mm oven for those aspiring chefs.
The second living room features a gas log fire place, full length feature hearth & floating display shelves.
Kingsize master bedroom with walk in robe & spacious ensuite.
Sliding glass doors lead out to the timber deck outdoor living area.
Well established gardens are a feature & a delight to meander around.
Double garage with internal access.
Located within easy walking distance to the town centre, local schools & sporting grounds.
Insights: 72 Princess Street, Drysdale VIC 3222 was last sold in 2016 and 35 other 4 bedroom house in Drysdale have recently been sold.

Description:
Beautiful Drysdale home centrally located.
Nestled behind beautiful box hedging and picket fence is the opportunity for you to find this stunning fully renovated period home located within walking to Drysdale. As you enter the home it greets you with warmth. Off the entry you will find the master bedroom with bay doors opening onto front deck and full ensuite. Also located off the entry is the other two large bedrooms with bedroom four/ office at the rear of the property and family bathroom with corner spa. Large kitchen area offering ample cupboard and bench space that can only be imagined with external access to covered alfresco area. Dining area sits opposite the kitchen opening out to deck area. The separate lounge offers gas log fire and exposed brick work. The undercover alfresco area has exposed aggregated concrete. The home features stunning 9' ceilings throughout, gas ducted heating, reverse cycle split system, ceiling fans, low maintenance gardens and garage.

Description:
Bellarine Peninsular Lifesyle
This beautiful property is situated on the outskirts of Drysdale high on the northern slopes of Murradoc Hill in close proximity to local olive groves, wineries and only a hop, skip and jump to Jack Rabbit vineyard. Realistically priced to sell.
The expansive views of Geelong and Corio Bay by day and by night are exquisite. Eight undulating acres lends itself to a quiet retreat on the edge of the blossoming Bellarine Peninsula. Beautiful rambling gardens surround the home and provide an atmosphere of peace and tranquillity with plenty of room for the pets.
The home has recently been refurbished from top to bottom - new floor coverings throughout, new window furnishings, new LED energy efficient lighting, painting to all internals, fully renovated bathroom, laundry and kitchen featuring a Falcon Elan cooker with gas hotplates, double electric ovens and grill, spacious Butler's pantry. The lounge room has an open fireplace and expansive views to the gardens, Bass Strait and the night lights of Geelong. The family area is heated by solid fuel heating and a reverse cycle air-conditioner.
A separate bungalow has brand new appliances - gas oven and hotplates, Rinnai energy-saver gas heater and HWS.
There is ample room for horses or a few cattle or sheep. Shedding includes two stables and a tack room with covered storage for the float. A new cattle race, refurbished yards and ample shedding for tradesmen complete this significant property.The property is serviced by town and tank water and has a septic recycling system suitable for use on the extended garden beds.
Situated within easy access to local schools and sporting facilities. Inspection is a must to appreciate the unique position of this lovely property. Inspection by appointment.
Rhonda Humpage : 0457 313 609

Description:
Classic Drysdale Gem
Nestled in a peaceful location this much loved and beautifully maintained family home presents a very inviting street appeal and classical design. Upon entry the master bedroom is generous in size and features bay windows, accompanied by a walk in robe and contemporary styled ensuite, with the private study adjacent providing a quiet area to set up the home office. Flowing through to the elegant formal dining and lounge area positioned in the heart of the home, with plenty of space for the whole family to enjoy.
A well-designed kitchen with quality built cabinetry and island bench includes a stainless steel cooktop, electric oven, all looking over an additional light-filled living area surrounded by views of the lush green gardens. Furthermore, this exceptional home comprises two additional bedrooms both with built in robes and serviced by a central bathroom with separate toilet and separate laundry. Step outside to the paved alfresco area ready to be enjoyed with family and friends, with a neat and manageable backyard, established trees and enough space for your own "Vegie Garden".
Extra features include a double garage with access to the backyard and enough room to store a caravan to the side, the comfort of ducted heating, and the great benefit of a solar system. Situated a short drive to the main hub of Drysdale and lifestyle pleasures of the world class Clifton Springs Golf Club, Boat Ramp, great local schools and local sporting facilities. Quite simply, a beautifully presented and well catered for property, a great opportunity to call home in a highly sought after pocket of Drysdale.

Description:
Prime Position Real Estate
This super central home sits metres from Drysdale's comprehensive shopping precinct. Set on 725sqm this property offers exciting options for a developer (STCA), or a perfect opportunity for first homebuyers searching for a central location and the ability to extend in the future (STCA). Close to Mc Leods Water Holes and the Drysdale Reserve, the position is convenient and lifestyle-orientated.
This well-maintained 3-bedroom cottage with a single carport is a comfortable and low maintenance home. Great shedding includes two separate 3x3m gardens sheds and a large 7x4m shed on the rear boundary that augurs well as a bungalow, entertaining space or 'man cave'. It offers ideal storage for a trades person.
The split-level design boasts lofty vaulted ceilings, exposed beams and a north-south aspect.
The living room is homely and relaxed and offers a near-new split system AC, Rinnai gas heater and ceiling fan. Full height windows frame views to the streetscape.
Meals boasts a bright northern aspect and connects to a large undercover outdoor entertaining area. The unique potbelly gas heater is effective and full of character.
The spotless kitchen features a large pantry, freestanding electric oven with gas cook top and spacious bench tops.
Step up to the bedrooms and wet areas, privately zoned away from the living areas. These include 3 inviting double bedrooms with full height glazing and garden views, a fresh contemporary bathroom with vanity, shower and large skylight, and a 2-way toilet that connects the bathroom and laundry.
The north-facing backyard offers a large secure lawn for children, pets and entertaining.
You won't find a more central home with so much potential! View ASAP!
Rhonda Humpage : 0457 313 609

Description:
Seriously, A Short Walk To Shops!
Originally this property was chosen because of its close proximity to Drysdale.
Approx. one kilometre walk to the Drysdale Shopping precinct but a quiet street when you are home. Solidly built 40 year old home that is on an 1100 square metre block of land. Many a game of home cricket played in this back yard. Room for parties too. Built ahead of its time with three bedrooms, two bathrooms and a study. Good plan for functional and family living. Drysdale is a historic town founded on farming back in the 1800's. It still has that country feel about it. Living here is easy all your requirements for every day are right at your fingertips.

Description:
Exceptional location
Four bedroom residence in one on Drysdale's coveted streets;a street steeped in history from the Crimea War days of mid-1800's. Offering two large separate living areas, one with a wood fire. Modern galley kitchen with a large servery window.
Freshly painted inside & out, with a rejuvenated tile roof.
Served by a circular driveway, there is plenty of room for the caravan, boat & truck.
Master bedroom with ensuite and walk in robe.
Freshly renovated central bathroom.
Polished hardwood timber floors are a feature throughout.
A large shed would suit the handyman or make a great mancave.
Just a short walk & you're ambling through the McLeod Waterholes reserve. Centrally located within easy access to the Drysdale Railway Station, new 24hr Woolworths service station, Bellarine Secondary College, St Ignatius College, St Thomas Catholic School & the township of Drysdale.

Description:
KIDS CAN WALK SAFELY TO SCHOOL!
Drysdale is a vibrant community that offers all the services and recreation at your fingertips. We all like to know that we have everything we require close at hand. No problem here, walking distance to schools, shops, medical centres and public transport. Living in Drysdale offers close proximity to golf courses, fishing beaches, surf beaches, restaurants, bike trails. So you can easily work, live and play in this historic town. This home is excellent for entertaining a crowd. Two separate living zones, main bedroom with ensuite and WIR at the front and open plan kitchen, meals, living at the rear with the other two bedrooms with BIRs. Large undercover area outside for the get together with family and friends. Very workable floorplan for families with kids of all ages, also suit downsizers who enjoy entertaining. When would you like me to arrange a time to view?

25 Acres
